						<div class="postbody">Thank you both for all advices.<br /><br />I took a closer look and it's a screw with a plastic head that says アース (earth) in front of a metal plate. So it's just a matter of screwing the metal plate on the fringe. No need for a cable shoe.<br /><br />The refrigerator though really doesn't have an earth cable. It does have two really short green &amp; yellow cables connecting something on the backside of it to the chassis but there are none going out of it that can be used to connect to the earth outlet. OK I will ask my landlord about it.</div>

					
